params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Required. The resource name of the policy to delete. Format: policies/{attachment_point}/denypolicies/{policy_id} Use the URL-encoded full resource name, which means that the forward-slash character, /, must be written as %2F. For example, policies/cloudresourcemanager.googleapis.com%2Fprojects%2Fmy-project/denypolicies/my-policy. For organizations and folders, use the numeric ID in the full resource name. For projects, you can use the alphanumeric or the numeric ID.

params.name: data.etag
params.description: Optional. The expected etag of the policy to delete. If the value does not match the value that is stored in IAM, the request fails with a 409 error code and ABORTED status. If you omit this field, the policy is deleted regardless of its current etag.
